  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.12256" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>Payne Theological Seminary,<lb/>Wilberforce, Ohio, 189?<lb/> Prof Schuchardt=</dateline>
        <opener>My dear Sir=</opener>

        <p> I am gathering all the information I can indicate in relation to the future of African „from a linguistic standpoint“ – as for example what will be the outcome of the <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.779">Spanish</ref>, <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.226">French</ref>, <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.844">Portuguese</ref>, <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.891">English</ref> languages in their relation to the African tongue – what as to the new languages forming from this mixture of tongues. Will you kindly give me whatever information you may feel disposed to write on the subject? I am interested in the subject and I shall prepare a paper on the same. Please oblige me by complying with this request. </p>
        <closer>
          <salute> Yours very sincerely</salute>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2604"> WSScarborough</persName> Professor etc etc </signed>
        </closer>
        <postscript>
          <p> [am Rand:] Please send all you can on African Philology and oblige WSb.</p>
        </postscript>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
